data.text: 3.2 All material will subject to our final inspection and approval at our works before acceptance However such inspection will not
absolve the vendor  of his responsibility for any defects in material/manufacturing/workmanship and subsequent rejections
and warranty returns on these account would be the responsibility or the vendor.
3.3 The Suppliers should be accompanied by supplier’s own detailed inspection report in duplicate.
3.4 Use or correct material conforming to the given specification must be ensured. Wherever applicable, the material Test Report
must accompany such consignment. However if at any later stage/data the material is found not conforming to our
specification, the entire liability for the compensation of  loss/damage caused/incurred will be of the vendor.
3.5 Rejection if any must be collected from our works within 10 days of receipt of such intimation, failing which the material will
be scrapped, returned at vendor’s risk and cost of the material including Taxes and Government levies paid and expenses
incurred in packing and forwarding as repacking/scrapping etc. will be debited to vendor’s account and the amount deducted
from the bills. We shall not accept any liability for losses or consequence to rejected material resulting during temporary
storage in our premises or while in transit for returning.
3.6 In case the order is for processing only for rejections arising out of material defects, material cost at the rate indicated
overleaf would be debited to the original supplier of material who should reimburse us the amount immediately.
3.7 For rejections from material delivered to us against payment through bank if returned documents for the said will be sent
3.8 Samples where required must be submitted as per the given schedule. In the events of delay or rejection of two consecutive
samples the order would be cancelled at no cost liability to us.
4.1Delivery is essence of this order and the suppliers must be made as per the schedules given failing which we reserve the
right to cancel the order without notice and refuse all subsequent deliveries Accepted quantities as per our inspection report
would be treated as the quantity delivered.
4.2 Deliveries should be accompanied by your challan and bill in triplicate clearly stating item description, Purchase Order
number, our drawing No. and item code, HSN/SAC Code and our drawings if supplied along with order.
4.3 For Deliveries should be affected within the notified hours (10.00 A.M. to 4.00 P.M.) on all working days.
4.4 Supplier in excess of the given schedule must not be made without prior written consent failing which excess  will not be
4.5 Packing slip clearly indicating item description, item No., Purchase order No. & Quantity must invariably accompany duty
fixed on each packing stipulated on the reverse.
4.6 We reserve the right to amend, postpone delivery schedule in accordance with our requirements.
4.7 This order is subject to cancellation at our option, if the performance regarding timely deliveries and quality of goods supplied
is not satisfactory we shall be free to arrange alternate purchase at vendor’s risk and cost in such cases, our decision will be
final and binding on the vendor.
4.8 For delivery of Hazardous chemicals/substances through transport vehicle, safety rules must be followed according to Indian
Motor Vehicle Act 1988 and any future amendments from time to time by government.
5.1Payment of the Bill/Invoices will be made within one month from the date of receipt of bill if not stipulated otherwise.
